# @VERSION spec:gdls v:0.1.0 generated:2026-04-18 source:schema-agent
# @FORMAT COLUMN|SQL_TYPE|NULLABLE|KEY|DESCRIPTION
# Project Atlas — schema as it stands after build migrations 001-014

@D atlas_finance|Atlas modernised ledger schema (Postgres 16) — post-build migration set

@T GeneralLedger|Account master — added closed_at index in migration 008
account_id|UUID|N|PK|Primary key
account_code|VARCHAR(40)|N||Chart of accounts code
account_name|VARCHAR(200)|N||Display name
status|VARCHAR(20)|N||Lifecycle status
parent_id|UUID|Y|FK|Parent account
currency_iso|CHAR(3)|N||ISO 4217 code
opened_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||When the account was opened
closed_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|Y||If closed, when (added migration 008)
created_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Row creation timestamp
updated_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Last mutation timestamp
@E GeneralLedger.status|ACTIVE,INACTIVE,CLOSED,FROZEN

@T JournalEntry|Journal entries — version + supersession + new validation_ok column from migration 011
entry_id|UUID|N|PK|Primary key
posting_date|DATE|N||Effective accounting date
account_id|UUID|N|FK|Account reference
amount|NUMERIC(28,8)|N||Posted amount
amount_base|NUMERIC(28,8)|Y||Base-currency translation
fx_rate|NUMERIC(18,8)|Y||FX rate snapshot
source_kind|VARCHAR(30)|N||Origin classification
source_event_id|UUID|Y||Upstream event identifier
posted_by|VARCHAR(120)|N||Service or user identity
posted_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Wall-clock timestamp
reverses_entry_id|UUID|Y|FK|Reversed entry
batch_id|UUID|Y|FK|Batch identifier
version|INTEGER|N||Increments on supersession
validation_ok|BOOLEAN|N||Set true after Validator runs (added migration 011)
@E JournalEntry.source_kind|MANUAL,PAYMENT,CDC,FX_REVAL,RECON_ADJUSTMENT,IMPORT

@T MigrationLog|Tracks applied migrations — added migration 001
migration_id|VARCHAR(40)|N|PK|Migration identifier (e.g. 0001_init)
applied_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||When the migration was applied
checksum|VARCHAR(64)|N||SHA-256 of the migration script

@T IdempotencyKey|Idempotency keys for posting consumers — added migration 005
key|VARCHAR(120)|N|PK|Idempotency key (typically Kafka topic + offset)
seen_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||When the event was first observed
entry_id|UUID|Y|FK|Resulting journal entry, if posted

@T ReconciliationGate|Per-period gate state — added migration 013
period|VARCHAR(7)|N|PK|YYYY-MM
threshold|NUMERIC(28,8)|N||Variance threshold (default 0.01)
gate_status|VARCHAR(20)|N||Current gate status
last_evaluated_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Last evaluation timestamp
@E ReconciliationGate.gate_status|OPEN,CLOSED,GATED,WAIVED

@R JournalEntry.account_id -> GeneralLedger.account_id|fk
@R JournalEntry.reverses_entry_id -> JournalEntry.entry_id|fk|Reversal linkage
@R IdempotencyKey.entry_id -> JournalEntry.entry_id|fk|Idempotency-to-entry traceability
